emand the development of environmentally friendly technology (replace those damn coal burning plants!), and basically give everyone around the world constitutional rights to free speech, press, etc.  The human race can only advance when people are free to speak their minds and express ideas even though that idea sometimes seems to backfire occassionally.  And of course the nuclear rockets would begin their assault on the solar system!   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 12/19/02 6:49:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1672<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/20/02 1:33:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/leela1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: World Domination and You!</span><hr size=1> Complete control, eh?  <br>
